column9: Can't wait until I play it

I have been playing this game for a couple of years, first the old Windows version (much easier) and now the Android version, which is very difficult in the higher levels. The first 20-25 levels are rather easy, but after that things get really tough. I think the game has been designed in such a way that will make us spend money in order to proceed from level to level. Perhaps I am wrong, but I doubt it is possible to accomplish any of the higher levels without buying a lot of extra stars.

Online functions do not work for some reason and crashes sometimes,  enemies become bullet sponges and tactics seem meeningless later in game. Spamming power ups seems to be the only way to progress in some late missions.

Toy Defense 2 would not allow me to upgrade unit positions in battle campaigns except for Stalingrad missions. The pace of this game also looks like ants marching in single file. If you like defense games like this then go for Kingdom Rush instead. It's not as linear as this game and animations are way better. And doesn't look like ants raiding your picnic basket.

I've played this game for a while now and I think I've obtained a very good understanding of it. I like to play strategically ( long term goals) rather than just dealing heavy damage, because of this I usually have a very balanced army compared to the current mission I'm on. I've noticed that sometimes your troops will ignore the passed troop ( closest to your base) rather than try to destroy it. Another bug I've noticed is sometimes ( currently the interceptor) doesn't lvl up when it should be. Plz fix.
